  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nExclusive to:\nSpicy Chili\nFood Info\n37.5\n20\n0\nMeat\nObject Info\nPerk\nIncreases temperature by 15 degrees over 15 seconds.\n10 Days\nCan be Burned\n40\nCooking Info\nx1.5 x1.5\n10 sec\n10\nMiscellaneous\n\"hotchili\"\n“Five alarm!”\n–Wilson\n“Now that's my kind of heat!”\n–Willow\n“Haha, nothing is too spicy for Wolfgang!”\n–Wolfgang\n“Burn my insides.”\n–Wendy\n“SPICE MAGNITUDE EXTREMELY HIGH”\n–WX-78\n“Chili gives me indigestion.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“Good after a long day of chopping in the cold.”\n–Woodie\n“Hot as heck!”\n–Maxwell\n“Letting off an incredible amount of thermal energy.”\n–Wagstaff\n“A test öf my willpöwer.”\n–Wigfrid\n“Flavor bombs!”\n–Webber\n“Yow! Burns my tongue SO GOOD.”\n–Walani\n“Spice up my life!”\n–Warly\n“Makes m'grateful me tongue's wooden.”\n–Woodlegs\n“IT MAKE'TH WILBA TONGUE GO'ST FWOOSH”\n–Wilba\n“Hot! It's hot!”\n–Wormwood\n“Smells like something burning.”\n–Wheeler\n“I'm tough enough to handle a little spice.”\n–Winona\n“I don't \"digest\" well.”\n–Wortox\n“Don't want it, florp!”\n–Wurt\n“Nothing warms you up like a big bowl of chili.”\n–Walter\n“Hoooo... I always forget just how spicy it is.”\n–Wanda\nSpicy Chili is a Meat Food item included in the Reign of Giants DLC. It can be cooked in the Crock Pot by combining 1.5 units of Meats and 1.5 units of Vegetables, except Peppers, which will result in Stuffed Pepper Poppers. No fillers are available for this recipe.\nAdding two Monster Foods will have a 50% chance of resulting in Monster Lasagna.\nWhen eaten, it will increase the character's temperature by 1 degree per second for 15 seconds.\nDownloadable Content[edit | edit source]\nSpicy Chili is also included in the Shipwrecked and Hamlet DLCs.\nPrerequisites[edit | edit source]\nRequires:\nRequires:\nRecipe[edit | edit source]\n×1.5\n×1.5\nExamples[edit | edit source]\n×2\nAdding Eel in place of Fish will result in Unagi\n×2\nAdding 2 Raw Seaweed will result in California Roll\n×2\n×2\n×2\n50% chance to result in Monster Lasagna\nTips[edit | edit source]\nThis food is relatively cheap to make, requiring only a Morsel, Monster Meat, and two farm vegetables. It is also quick to prepare in a Crock Pot, requiring 10 seconds of cooking time. If one can manage to preserve vegetables long enough or find them quickly, this food can be particularly useful during Winter as it increases perceived temperature.\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nIcon used as emoji for Official Klei Discord\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
